						<summary>

						<p>Wooden beam in the Huḍēda Hanumappa temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya A.D. 1519.</p>						

						<p>This inscription referring itself to the reign of Kṛishṇarāya is dated in the cyclic year Bahudhānya, Phālguṇa śu. 10 corresponding to A.D. 1519, February 9, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>It states that the temple was built for the merit of Tirumalappa, an officer of Bāgila Timmappa-nāyaka, by his son-in-law Ayirāpiḷa. In characters of about 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
